Maas

Maas is the name of a river that is also named Meuse.
Surname.
Maas also is a Dutch and North German surname. It can be toponymic ("from the Maas river"), but usually is of patronymic origin (Maas being a nickname for Thomas). The surname is quite common in the Netherlands, ranking 43rd in 2007 (16,070 people). People with this name include:

