Using thermodynamics (chemical potential).
Quantities here are given per molecule, not per mole, and so Boltzmann constant and the electron charge are used instead of the gas constant and Faraday's constant . To convert to the molar quantities given in most chemistry textbooks, it is simply necessary to multiply by Avogadro's number: and .
